<div class="story-body">
    <p>Trade statistics show that by 2015, China earned almost $9 for every dollar that U.S earned from exports to Africa. This is revealing of the extent to which China has captured the African market.</p>
    <p>China’s top exports to Africa include machinery, electronics and textiles.  And its top imports are crude oil, iron ore, cotton and other natural resources. South Africa, Angola and Nigeria are its biggest trading partners on the continent.</p>
    <p>The surge in China-Africa trade volume has been bolstered by export credit facilitation that Africa importers receive from Chinese government owned banks. The Brookings in 2018 reported that China has been awarding import credit worth $35 billion annually to African importers or Chinese companies exporting goods to Africa.</p>


</div>


